# C++ & Vulkan Standards (Mobile-First)

Applies to `next/nlrc_vksplat/` only.

## Language & platform

- C++17
- Headless Vulkan in `next/nlrc_vksplat/src/` — no Win32, XCB, or other windowing APIs in core library code

## Memory alignment (ARM64)

Mobile GPUs are sensitive to alignment. Host/device structs, push constants (max 192 bytes), and storage-buffer layouts must strictly match `std430`. Mirror layouts in C++ with `alignas()` — do not rely on `PACK_STRUCT` or implicit packing from the reference.

## Vulkan extensions

- Prefer core Vulkan 1.2 and universally supported extensions
- Make desktop-only extensions optional (e.g. `VK_EXT_subgroup_size_control` must not be required on OHOS)

## Maleoon 910 profile (audit every port)

- Compute workgroup sizes ≤ 512
- Subgroup size 64 (not 32)
- Enable `VKSPLAT_USE_EMULATED_INT64` and `VKSPLAT_USE_EMULATED_F32_ATOMIC` when hardware lacks native support

## Descriptor model

- Descriptor set 0: sequential `VK_DESCRIPTOR_TYPE_STORAGE_BUFFER` bindings 0..N-1
- Push constants: camera, step, learning rates, image size, etc.
- No textures — all data in storage buffers

## Abstractions

Reuse rewrite abstractions once introduced (`VulkanGSPipeline`, `_VulkanBuffer`, `Buffer<T>`, `_ComputePipeline`). Do not copy ref internals (`PACK_STRUCT`, `_THROW_ERROR`) without reason.
